After reopening VSCode, Vendordeps that had previously been error-free were highlighted red.


I can still build, so it’s not a critical error, but it makes it difficult to debug and write further code. It’s worth noting that WPILib imports are not sending errors. Has this happened to anybody else, and how did you fix it?

[EDIT] I was able to remove the errors by uninstalling and reinstalling the libraries, but I fear that this is just a temporary solution.

Generally if building is still successful, but VSCode still shows red squiggles, then its simply an intellisense error. There are ways to fix that without reinstalling vendor deps. I’m on my phone, so I’ll let others provide specifics so I don’t misspeak, but they’re also mentioned on nearly every thread that mentions a similar error (red underline but successful build)
